cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

The paper proposes a bio-inspired Convolutional Spiking Neural Network (CSNN) for object recognition in natural images. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Systems and Control (cs.SY). However, given the focus on neural networks and image processing, cs.NE and cs.CV are the most likely categories. The use of unsupervised and supervised learning algorithms also suggests a focus on machine learning, which further supports the inclusion of cs.LG and cs.AI as likely categories. Finally, the mention of plasticity in the neural network suggests a possible focus on control systems, which could include cs.SY as a possible category.
